title: CARiD.com Adds Luxury Body Kits from Liberty Walk to Extensive Product Catalogue
text:
CARiD.com
Automotive ecommerce retailer to be an authorized seller of Liberty Walk's full product line of approximately 175 parts
CRANBURY, N.J. , Oct. 20, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- CARiD.com, an online retailer of all things automotive and more, today announced it has added luxury body kits from Liberty Walk to it's growing catalogue of available brands. CARiD.com began carrying Liberty Walk's product line at the end of August of this year.
Photo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151019/278471
As an official authorized reseller for Liberty Walk , CARiD.com will offer the Japan -based company's entire 175-item product line of luxury body kits, with offerings for BMW, Ferrari, Lamborghini, Porsche, Chrysler, Dodge, Nissan/Infiniti, and Toyota. CARiD.com will also offer shipping direct from Liberty Walk's Japanese manufacturing center straight to the customer's front door.
"We're thrilled to be able to offer our customers even more variety in terms of customization of their favorite car, especially those looking for a higher-end product and luxury look," said Leslie Pritchard , Marketing Specialist, CARiD.com. "We take great pride in customer satisfaction, and adding Liberty Walk products to our online catalogue is another step toward continuing to give our customers what they want – quality products and a level of personalization to make their car their own."
Started in a lot large enough to display only three cars, Liberty Walk has grown into one of the most recognized aftermarket brands in Japan and the world. For more information, please visit www.libertywalk-usa.com .
CARiD.com's mission is to revolutionize the online shopping experience for the automotive parts and accessories industry by providing its customers with the top brands available on the market, and a customer service experience to match. For more information, please visit http://www.CARiD.com .
About CARiD.com
CARiD.com has become one of the fastest growing aftermarket automotive online retailers by offering the widest variety of parts, using state of the art technologies, and employing the most dedicated and creative team members in the industry.
Based in Cranbury, NJ , CARiD.com caters to the needs of all levels of automotive enthusiasts worldwide – from the do-it-yourselfer home mechanic to custom shops and dealers.
